text.section:
Disclosures required under this statute shall be provided at any of the following times or as otherwise provided by law:
Upon submitting a provider application;
Upon executing a provider agreement;
Upon request of the Cabinet for Health and Family Services during a provider's revalidation of enrollment;
Within thirty-five (35) days after any change in ownership of a health facility or health service, fiscal agent, or managed care entity;
Upon the submission of a proposal in accordance with the state's procurement process by a fiscal agent or by a managed care entity;
Upon execution, renewal, or extension of a contract by the state with a fiscal agent or a managed care entity; or
Upon written request within thirty-five (35) days by the Cabinet for Health and Family Services.
